1
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:09,100
No one is leaving!
No one is going anywhere!

2
00:00:09,233 --> 00:00:10,733
After everything you did?

3
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:12,667
You still have the nerve
to stay in this house!

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:13,467
[GRUMBLES]

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,100
So, that is your decision.

6
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:17,600
I am not a wife who can endure
like you, Mom.

7
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:19,300
Did they leave? Where are they?

8
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:22,200
They are not answering
my calls anymore.

9
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,367
Is it true?

10
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,933
Did they cheat?

11
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,533
Is this my fault?

12
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:27,967
My child, I am sorry.

13
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:29,900
I never wanted you to go
through this.

14
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,733
A family like this.

15
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:33,967
Are you really that desperate
for our wealth?

16
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:37,867
Do you really think you will
still gain anything from this?

17
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,733
One signature from me,
and you are out.

18
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:29,933
[SOBBING]

19
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:40,000
[DRAMATIC]

20
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:44,867
Marjorie, I did not let Paolo
come here

21
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:47,433
because I know he is the last
person you want to see

22
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:48,767
right now.

23
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:54,200
So, that is your decision.

24
00:01:56,367 --> 00:01:57,967
Edward, what is this?

25
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,533
Dad said no one is leaving.

26
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:01,233
No one is going anywhere!

27
00:02:01,367 --> 00:02:03,767
Let Marj be the one to leave.

28
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:07,267
After everything I did just
to be accepted into this house?

29
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:09,533
After everything you did?

30
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:10,933
You have some nerve!

31
00:02:11,067 --> 00:02:13,200
You still have the
nerve to stay here!

32
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,500
Start packing your things.

33
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:15,733
No!

34
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,133
This is also mine
and Ashley's home,

35
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:19,100
and we have rights
to this house.

36
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:21,167
How are you going to explain
this to Jasmine?

37
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:25,967
You know her condition.

38
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:32,167
You know, she will get stressed
if you and Paolo separate,

39
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:37,500
and that will weaken her body
and compromise her treatment.

40
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:40,300
I do not want my child
to get hurt.

41
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:43,967
No mother wants their child
to get hurt.

42
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:48,833
You know, when I first found out
Greg had another woman,

43
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:54,267
I was angry, insulted, and hurt.

44
00:02:55,067 --> 00:02:55,967
Name it.

45
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:58,600
But I did not leave.

46
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:02,500
That woman, is she someone close
to you?

47
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:05,700
Was she also living
in this house

48
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:08,467
and doing her miracles here?

49
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:09,833
Yes.

50
00:03:09,967 --> 00:03:11,767
I have had my share of
experiences

51
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,267
where my husband betrayed me
in this house.

52
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:19,267
Was it not even the mother
of my daughter-in-law?

53
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:21,733
You stripped Ashley of her
rights here

54
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:23,767
the moment you brought scandal
into this house!

55
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:27,633
Dad, please,
let us just stay here.

56
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:28,533
See?

57
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,500
Even your child does
not want to leave.

58
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:34,333
Come on, Edward.

59
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:35,733
Everyone is still
drunk with anger.

60
00:03:35,867 --> 00:03:38,200
Do not make decisions
at a time like this.

61
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:41,233
What? Are you leaving?
Are you abandoning us?

62
00:03:41,367 --> 00:03:42,567
You are abandoning your child?

63
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:45,800
Do you really want all of us
to stay together in this hell?

64
00:03:45,933 --> 00:03:49,633
Oh, then let us all suffer
together in this hellhole.

65
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:51,933
But I am not leaving!

66
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:55,167
I would rather we all turn
to ashes

67
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:58,167
than lose my place
in this family.

68
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:01,633
I am not a wife who can
endure like you, Mom.

69
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:04,100
I did not endure
because I wanted to.

70
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:08,367
I chose to as a mother.

71
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:14,300
So, Marj, maybe for now,
do not see Paolo as a husband,

72
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:16,233
but as Jasmine's father.

73
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:22,133
When you become a mother,

74
00:04:22,267 --> 00:04:24,100
decisions carry
a different weight.

75
00:04:25,767 --> 00:04:29,067
That is why I chose to preserve
the idea of a home,

76
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:31,767
because I did not want
my children to grow up

77
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,367
in a broken home.

78
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:39,967
Can you take away from Jasmine
the belief

79
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:42,233
that your family is still whole?

80
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:45,200
Mom, I do not want us
to fall apart.

81
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,467
Please, Dad.

82
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:51,167
[GRUMBLES]

83
00:04:53,133 --> 00:04:54,100
Papa!

84
00:04:54,233 --> 00:04:55,033
Dad!

85
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:58,033
[SOBBING]

86
00:04:58,167 --> 00:04:59,500
We are not leaving.

87
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:01,100
Your father just needs
to cool down.

88
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:05,367
As long as you want,
we will stay here.

89
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,333
And my father will not leave us.

90
00:05:07,467 --> 00:05:10,567
[DRAMATIC]

91
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,767
[SOBBING]

92
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:17,500
I do not know which truth
will kill her.

93
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:23,533
The truth, or us staying
in this house.

94
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:26,300
The truth can wait.

95
00:05:27,933 --> 00:05:29,233
But a child's hope,

96
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:33,567
when clinging to something worth
living for,

97
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:38,300
once broken,
can never be restored.

98
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:42,167
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

99
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:49,000
Are you okay, Mom?

100
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,400
I am just tired, my child.

101
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:53,467
Later, when we get home...

102
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,367
I am excited to go home, Mom.

103
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:59,967
The doctor said my reaction
to the treatment is good.

104
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:02,200
We can spend time together
again.

105
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,633
Family time with Dad.

106
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:05,000
Even if it is simple.

107
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:08,300
[DRAMATIC]

108
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:10,167
I missed all of you so much,
Mom.

109
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:13,233
Dad, Ashley,

110
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:14,567
Grandpa and Grandma,

111
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:16,700
Uncle, and Aunt.

112
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:18,367
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

113
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,800
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

114
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:25,533
[CLAMORING]

115
00:06:25,667 --> 00:06:26,633
Mom...

116
00:06:28,933 --> 00:06:30,000
What is this?

117
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:33,467
Why did you do that
to Dad and Aunt Thea?

118
00:06:34,933 --> 00:06:36,067
Jas, I am sorry.

119
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,667
Jas, stop!

120
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,767
<i> Why are you doing this?</i>

121
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,067
<i> On what basis?</i>

122
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:45,167
<i>Ask them and your sibling
what they were doing</i>

123
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,367
<i> behind our backs.</i>

124
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:51,833
Is it true what you are saying
in this video?

125
00:06:51,967 --> 00:06:53,733
Did they cheat?

126
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:54,933
Jas...

127
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,100
Jas, stop watching that.

128
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:02,433
I am sorry, my child.

129
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:05,100
I am sorry you had to find out
this way.

130
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,433
Mom, please.

131
00:07:07,567 --> 00:07:08,767
I want to go home.

132
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:10,033
I want to talk to Dad.

133
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:11,200
Listen to me.

134
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:14,767
When we get home later,
we will pack our things, okay?

135
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:16,600
Mom, please do not do this.

136
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:19,333
Please, do not give up
right away.

137
00:07:19,467 --> 00:07:20,967
Dad might have an explanation.

138
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:22,567
There might be a reason
for everything.

139
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,767
We cannot just leave the house.

140
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,733
What will happen to us?

141
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:28,333
I want to protect you.

142
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:30,967
I just do not want you
to get hurt.

143
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:33,833
But I am hurting more this way,
Mom.

144
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:36,133
It feels like we
are running away.

145
00:07:36,267 --> 00:07:38,167
Can we not just talk first?

146
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,467
Maybe when Dad sees me,

147
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:43,700
you will both realize
that we need each other.

148
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:46,400
Maybe when the three of us
face each other,

149
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:48,100
we can find a way to fix this.

150
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:49,233
Please.

151
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:52,533
[DRAMATIC]

152
00:07:52,667 --> 00:07:54,233
Did they leave?

153
00:07:54,367 --> 00:07:56,000
Their things are still upstairs.

154
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:57,233
Where are they?

155
00:07:57,367 --> 00:07:59,000
Mom, you told me you
would handle this.

156
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:01,967
I tried to talk to her, but...

157
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,033
There is only so much--

158
00:08:03,167 --> 00:08:06,133
They are not answering my calls
anymore.

159
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:08,267
Try again.

160
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,933
I will go to the hospital
for now.

161
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,333
They might still be there
with Jasmine.

162
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:12,433
Nanny!

163
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:13,900
Nanny, please get my keys!

164
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:14,833
Nanny!

165
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:16,933
- Please, get my keys!
- Nanny, please!

166
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,100
Where is Oscar?

167
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,567
Love, Marj.

168
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:25,333
Thank God.

169
00:08:25,467 --> 00:08:27,467
I thought...

170
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,633
I came back here for Jasmine.

171
00:08:30,567 --> 00:08:32,867
She insisted that we come home.

172
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:36,567
She has questions.

173
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:39,000
Let us not involve
the child in this.

174
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:41,433
You have a lot of explaining
to do, Dad.

175
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:44,300
My child, it is complicated.

176
00:08:44,433 --> 00:08:47,133
Dad, I thought nothing was
too complicated for us.

177
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:51,333
Did you not say we are a team?

178
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:54,967
What is complicated is chemo.

179
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:00,067
Waking up every day not knowing
if I will be okay.

180
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,800
But this?

181
00:09:06,533 --> 00:09:09,433
Dad, I came home
because I want us to fix this.

182
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:12,433
Please, tell me we
can still fix this.

183
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:16,100
That it was not your choice
to hurt Mom and me.

184
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:19,633
I just need to hear
that you still love us.

185
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:24,500
That this family is still enough
reason for you to fight.

186
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,200
Just like how I fought
my illness.

187
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:36,633
Mom, Dad, please.

188
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:39,667
Let us not let this end
like this.

189
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,000
I survived the hospital

190
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:46,200
because I thought I was coming
home to a complete family.

191
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,933
Can we please just talk
about this?

192
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:53,233
Let us fix this, please.

193
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:58,800
[DRAMATIC]

194
00:10:04,733 --> 00:10:06,400
And that is what happened,
my child.

195
00:10:08,267 --> 00:10:09,633
Daddy made a mistake.

196
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:13,767
One huge mistake, Dad.

197
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,733
Is this my fault?

198
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,800
Jasmine, you did nothing wrong.

199
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,700
No, my child.

200
00:10:26,433 --> 00:10:27,733
It is not your fault.

201
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:32,200
Because ever since I got sick,
Mom,

202
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,500
you have been taking care of me
all the time.

203
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:37,700
You no longer have time.

204
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:41,400
You worry about nothing else
but me.

205
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:46,300
And you and Dad keep fighting.

206
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:49,567
Did you get tired, Dad?

207
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:52,767
Maybe that is why you
looked for someone else,

208
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,867
because I am the problem.

209
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,000
No, my child.

210
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:59,300
You are not the problem.

211
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:01,400
You did not choose to be sick.

212
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,367
But...

213
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:07,867
A person is at fault
when they choose to be weak.

214
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:12,767
When they choose to give in
to temptation

215
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,233
instead of standing firm.

216
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,267
Marj, please,
not in front of the child.

217
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:21,200
What do you want?

218
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:23,667
Should we lie again?

219
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:27,967
The child deserves to know
how you did this to us.

220
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:30,900
She asked to hear everything.

221
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:34,667
How you chose
to destroy our family.

222
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:44,367
[DRAMATIC]

223
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:49,900
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:56,367
Dad?

225
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:58,267
Dad!

226
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:02,067
Dad.

227
00:12:07,233 --> 00:12:10,833
Ash, why are you still awake?

228
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,433
Dad.

229
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,500
It's already afternoon.

230
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:25,500
I wish you had just
slept in your room.

231
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:29,033
Mom slept in my room
last night too.

232
00:12:36,633 --> 00:12:39,467
I hate seeing you like this,
Dad.

233
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,567
You are my constant.

234
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:51,867
When you are unstable,

235
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:57,067
I have nothing left
to hold on to.

236
00:12:58,767 --> 00:12:59,900
My child, I am sorry.

237
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:05,167
You see us like this.

238
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,300
I never wanted you
to experience this.

239
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:13,567
A family like this.

240
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:15,867
Dad...

241
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:19,367
Dad.

242
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,600
[SOBBING]

243
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:22,000
I am sorry, my child.

244
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:26,200
I am sorry to you and your mom.

245
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:29,767
This is all on me.

246
00:13:32,567 --> 00:13:35,467
Not because something
was lacking at home.

247
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:39,833
Not because you failed
in any way.

248
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:42,700
My child,
not because you are sick.

249
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,633
It is me.

250
00:13:45,767 --> 00:13:47,867
I am the one who failed.

251
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,267
My child, I am sorry you
have to go through this.

252
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:55,400
At your age.

253
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,300
In your condition.

254
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:00,233
I am not a child, Dad.

255
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,533
But I still do not deserve
to be in this situation.

256
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:06,967
Mom does not deserve this
either.

257
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:10,033
[DRAMATIC]

258
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:11,267
I'm sorry, my child.

259
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:16,133
And if I could take back...

260
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:24,100
the days when I chose to
continue this mistake, my child,

261
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:28,633
even if it is wrong,
I would do it.

262
00:14:33,167 --> 00:14:34,733
I am just tired, Dad.

263
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:39,700
At least with cancer,
I know what is happening.

264
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:42,833
There is a schedule, tests,
and a plan.

265
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:46,467
But this?

266
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:49,800
I do not know.

267
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,567
What are you going to do
for Mom?

268
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,333
For us?

269
00:15:02,133 --> 00:15:04,433
Because I do not think
I can handle being sick

270
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,467
and then watching you separate.

271
00:15:08,867 --> 00:15:11,500
Dad, please,
you have to do something.

272
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:16,133
I just want Mom to still
be here, with you,

273
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:17,333
with us.

274
00:15:17,467 --> 00:15:18,500
Please.

275
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:22,333
[SOBBING]

276
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:23,600
Yes, my child.

277
00:15:23,733 --> 00:15:26,733
[DRAMATIC]

278
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:29,533
[SOBBING]

279
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,467
It is okay, Dad.

280
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:41,467
[SOBBING]

281
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,233
I tried.

282
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:45,167
I really tried, my child.

283
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:53,967
Your mom and I have not
been okay for a long time,

284
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,233
but I endured it.

285
00:15:57,233 --> 00:15:58,567
Because I thought...

286
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:04,667
if I did nothing,
everything would be fine.

287
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,067
But it was not.

288
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,400
I do not know if this is
the price of that choice.

289
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:16,400
I am sorry we lied to you.

290
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:23,633
Dad.

291
00:16:23,767 --> 00:16:24,700
Dad...

292
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:29,433
someone told me...

293
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:35,633
that adults lie when they are
afraid to admit

294
00:16:35,767 --> 00:16:37,533
that something
is no longer working.

295
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,333
I just want...

296
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:48,200
everything to be okay
for our family.

297
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:51,767
For you.

298
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,867
You said you wanted
to stay here.

299
00:16:57,633 --> 00:16:59,900
I want to stay here

300
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:02,733
because our whole family
is here.

301
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:07,100
And I do not want you to
be far from your parents.

302
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:12,433
And I know that Mom
does not want to leave.

303
00:17:18,733 --> 00:17:26,700
But I also do not want to live
in a house filled with chaos.

304
00:17:27,933 --> 00:17:31,367
[SOBBING]

305
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:41,467
If there is a place, even small,
even simple...

306
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:45,367
as long as it is peaceful
and I am with you and Mom...

307
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,733
that is enough.

308
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,867
Let us go there.

309
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:56,900
Now.

310
00:17:58,467 --> 00:18:00,267
[SOBBING]

311
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:15,367
They really have a lot of nerve,
Sir Paolo and Ma'am Thea,

312
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:15,533
do they not?

313
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:17,800
Next thing we know,

314
00:18:17,933 --> 00:18:19,700
they are doing their indecency
all over the mansion.

315
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:22,833
So, you know, what Ma'am Marj
did to them was just right.

316
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,167
I admire her.

317
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:25,600
[SHUSHES]

318
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:26,733
Keep your voice down.

319
00:18:26,867 --> 00:18:30,100
But Sir Greg said
no one is leaving.

320
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:32,400
He wants everyone
to keep living here.

321
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:33,200
Oh my!

322
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:34,433
How is that supposed to work?

323
00:18:34,567 --> 00:18:36,800
It is like there is a planted
bomb in the living room.

324
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:38,733
That is why only Ma'am Marj
would have the courage

325
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:39,833
to do something.

326
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:40,800
But you are right.

327
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:43,267
Good luck if our employers
even allow it.

328
00:18:45,133 --> 00:18:48,867
But the guard said something
is already spreading

329
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,000
in the village group chat.

330
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:54,700
They say this is not the
first scandal in this mansion.

331
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:55,500
Oh my!

332
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:57,333
Should we even be surprised?

333
00:18:57,467 --> 00:19:00,333
This house has so many secrets,
does it not?

334
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:04,500
More will come out.

335
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:06,367
This will not be the last.

336
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:10,833
You are surprised, are you not?

337
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:15,800
The secrets of this house
are slowly coming out.

338
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:20,200
No matter how much you
suppress or clean it,

339
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:23,833
even if you shut all the doors
and windows,

340
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:28,767
you still cannot stop the lies
of this house from spreading.

341
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,867
I have lived here
for a long time.

342
00:19:34,267 --> 00:19:37,733
And because I have witnessed
what happens here for so long,

343
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:40,867
I know when it will finally
collapse.

344
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,167
Even if you try to save it.

345
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:53,500
[INTENSE]

346
00:19:53,633 --> 00:19:56,167
It will fall on its own.

347
00:20:02,733 --> 00:20:04,500
[KNOCKS]

348
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,067
Dad?

349
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:26,733
Dad, thank you
for letting us stay.

350
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:31,333
I really appreciate your efforts
to keep the family together.

351
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:35,367
I promise it will
never happen again.

352
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:37,033
You already said that before.

353
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:39,167
Sixteen years ago.

354
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:42,800
When you first ruined my
two children's lives.

355
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:47,633
That was a long time ago.

356
00:20:47,767 --> 00:20:48,733
This is different.

357
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:52,067
I fixed the mess you
caused back then.

358
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,367
I covered it up.

359
00:20:57,933 --> 00:20:59,333
I silenced it.

360
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:03,167
I made someone else
take the blame.

361
00:21:05,033 --> 00:21:06,533
I accepted the child.

362
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:09,300
Because the child
is my grandchild.

363
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:14,467
That is not what I meant.

364
00:21:20,767 --> 00:21:23,700
And now, you are doing it again.

365
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:25,833
So, tell me, Thea.

366
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:30,067
How long will you keep
feeding temptation?

367
00:21:31,533 --> 00:21:37,267
How long will you test
how much I can cover up?

368
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,767
Dad, you are hurting me.

369
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,667
Are you really that desperate
for our wealth?

370
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:45,167
That you had to betray
both of my children?

371
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,567
You already have a spouse.

372
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:49,900
You already have a child.

373
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:52,500
You are already
living in my house.

374
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:54,833
And still,
you are not satisfied.

375
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,367
Do you really think...

376
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:04,167
that what you are doing will
still benefit you in this hell?

377
00:22:06,467 --> 00:22:09,100
You will inherit
nothing here, dear.

378
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:12,200
You have no shares.

379
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,867
Ashley does.

380
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,067
Because Ashley is our blood.

381
00:22:17,233 --> 00:22:19,000
And you?

382
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:22,333
All you have is the Torrecampo
name attached to you.

383
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:25,800
One word from me.

384
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,133
One signature from me,
and you are out.

385
00:22:32,067 --> 00:22:36,833
[INTENSE]

386
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:43,467
Now, if you want to stay
in this house,

387
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:47,567
you do exactly as I say.

388
00:22:49,567 --> 00:22:55,967
I am letting you stay here
because of my grandchild.

389
00:22:57,567 --> 00:23:00,733
But you still do not know
your place

390
00:23:00,867 --> 00:23:02,667
and refuse to stop your indecent
behavior,

391
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,633
I will close more than just
doors on you.

392
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:14,667
Get out of my sight.

393
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:29,667
[INTENSE]

394
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:46,400
[SUSPENSEFUL]

395
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,833
<i>I have never done anything right
in your eyes!</i>

396
00:24:10,967 --> 00:24:14,167
<i>You treat me like I am not even
your real child!</i>

397
00:24:15,633 --> 00:24:17,267
<i> You are worthless!</i>

398
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:18,067
<i> [WHIMPERS]</i>

399
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:19,467
<i> And now I am the one at fault?</i>

400
00:24:20,333 --> 00:24:21,833
<i>- Greg! Greg!
- Dad!</i>

401
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:24,500
<i> You have humiliated me again!</i>

402
00:24:24,633 --> 00:24:28,267
<i>You wasted what little trust
I had left!</i>

403
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,967
<i> You are such a loser!</i>

404
00:24:30,133 --> 00:24:32,400
<i>Never challenge
your older brother!</i>

405
00:24:32,533 --> 00:24:33,700
<i> You still side with Paolo</i>

406
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:35,367
<i>even though I am the one wronged
here?</i>

407
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:36,533
<i> I am your child too!</i>

408
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:38,633
<i> For once, try to be fair!</i>

409
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:40,100
<i> To hell with this house!</i>

410
00:24:40,233 --> 00:24:41,733
<i> This family feels cursed.</i>

411
00:24:41,867 --> 00:24:43,033
<i> It just keeps repeating!</i>

412
00:24:43,167 --> 00:24:46,300
<i>This house, this family,
should burn!</i>

413
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:48,400
<i> Because this house is hell!</i>

414
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:54,433
[THUMPS, GLASS SHATTERS]

415
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:57,667
[INTENSE]

416
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,333
My God!

417
00:25:00,467 --> 00:25:03,333
Sir Edward,
what did you do?

418
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:07,733
[INTENSE]

419
00:25:07,867 --> 00:25:09,467
I will clean this up!

420
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:11,167
No!

421
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:13,400
Just leave it like that.

422
00:25:13,533 --> 00:25:14,833
Someone might see it.

423
00:25:14,967 --> 00:25:16,067
Then let them see it.

424
00:25:17,967 --> 00:25:20,900
So that painting matches
what is really happening

425
00:25:21,033 --> 00:25:22,833
to the family
inside this house.

426
00:25:24,167 --> 00:25:25,467
Broken!

427
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:26,600
Shattered!

428
00:25:27,833 --> 00:25:28,567
[HUFFS]

429
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:33,533
[INTENSE]

430
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:39,300
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

431
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:49,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

432
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:04,967
Do you think it is a wise idea
to keep them all under one roof?

433
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:06,933
We have other properties anyway.

434
00:26:07,067 --> 00:26:09,733
Maybe it is better
to separate them for now

435
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:10,933
while emotions are still high.

436
00:26:11,067 --> 00:26:12,800
We have to contain
the situation.

437
00:26:12,933 --> 00:26:16,267
The story becomes harder
if they are separated.

438
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,300
Stop it!

439
00:26:17,433 --> 00:26:19,033
We will live in the same house,

440
00:26:19,167 --> 00:26:21,067
but do not expect me
to be your wife.

441
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:22,367
Nothing has changed.

442
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:24,967
I will never forgive you, Paolo.

443
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:27,567
I am staying here for
our daughter's survival.

444
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:29,967
And as far as I know
and am concerned,

445
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:31,533
our marriage is dead.

446
00:26:31,667 --> 00:26:34,333
You and Paolo both have a huge
offense against me!

447
00:26:34,467 --> 00:26:35,667
You knew about Ashley, Dad.

448
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:39,233
You and Paolo,
you are such a worthless father!

449
00:26:39,367 --> 00:26:39,800
[THUDS]

450
00:26:39,933 --> 00:26:41,133
[GRUNTS]

451
00:26:41,267 --> 00:26:42,100
That is right.

452
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,600
I will take back
control of this family.

453
00:26:44,733 --> 00:26:47,400
All of us will stay
together in this house,

454
00:26:47,533 --> 00:26:49,100
even if we suffer.

455
00:26:49,233 --> 00:26:51,700
As long as this family
stays together.

456
00:26:51,833 --> 00:26:53,700
Who did this?

457
00:26:53,833 --> 00:26:55,133
Who?
